  "paper_ready_summary": "Across 7 detector backbones, compatibility-aware augmentation improves event F1 for 4 detectors against real_only and for 1 detectors against naive cross-dataset transfer. The mean event-F1 delta is 0.0106 for compatibility_strict over real_only and 0.0029 for cross_dataset_compatible over cross_dataset_all. These results should be interpreted as stability evidence, not as a final detector-level claim without broader multi-seed, dataset-balanced runs."
